      "date": "2012-06-05 19:25:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: (1 inline comment)\n\nDespite this patch only being a week old, it is not using tabs for indentation. This should be clearly causing many warnings to be printed from checkpatch.pl, so either those warnings are being ignored (bad), or the latest git commit hooks are not being used (also bad).\n\nPlease ensure that any systems used for development have the latest git commit hooks installed:\n\n ln -sf ../../build/commit-msg .git/hooks/\n ln -sf ../../build/prepare-commit-msg .git/hooks/\n\nand please pay attention to the warnings produced.",
